Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Boil a large #pot{} of salted water for the potatoes.

Chop the @potatoes{3} into 2cm chunks (peeling optional).

Add the potatoes to the boiling water and cook until fork tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain the potatoes in a #colander{} and return to the pan off the heat.

Add a knob of @butter{to taste} and a splash of @water{to taste} or @?milk{to taste}. Mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth, season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} then cover to keep warm.

While the potatoes are boiling, trim the @carrot{2} then quarter lengthways (no need to peel). Finely chop the @chives{5%grams}.

Pop the carrots onto a large (lined) #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{to taste}, season with @paprika{1%sachet}, @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} then toss to coat.

Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until tender, ~{20-25%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

In a #small bowl{}, combine the @yoghurt{75%grams}, @mustard{1%sachet} and chopped chives.

Season to taste with salt and pepper.

When the veg has 5 mins left to cook, melt @butter{1%tbsp}(double for 4p) in a pan over medium heat.

Add the @haddock{250%grams} and fry, ~{2-3%minutes} on each side, or until cooked through. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish. The fish is cooked when opaque in the middle. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide the carrots and potato between plates.

Serve the haddock alongside, drizzling over any buttery juices from the pan.

Serve the yoghurt chive sauce on the side.